This paper deals with the constraint satisfaction problem (CSP) and its generalization, valued constraint problems, which are central topics in artificial intelligence and computer science. The paper discusses the tractability of valued constraint problems and introduces novel hybrid classes of such problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses the notion of forbidden substructures, which is a common tool in computational complexity theory, suggesting that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems, which are often studied in the sub-category cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
